Worst movie ever made.  Corey Feldman, please, please please stop making movies.  Nobody wants to see your work.  How can you expect anyone to buy this thing.  My 10 year old nephew could make a better movie with his flip cam.

Terror Inside gave me the creeps--and a couple of scenes actually had me hiding my face in a pillow  But some of the other scenes were painfully disturbing to watch, and I still shudder just thinking about them. If you like being scared.. This is for you

I didn't know what to expect when I got this DVD.Another direct to DVD for Feldman like Lost Boys2. I didn't care for Lost Boys2 because Feldman is playing that "Feldman Character" he developed in his teens.

Well, that's over, which is an improvment. Although Corey often looks like he's disinterested or hardly working, he gives us insight to some possible acting skill. The movie starts in a small town and progresses to the point of gory bloodiness. Maybe too gory for some or not enough for others, this is not a Hollywood studio picture and it shows. Lacking in slick lighting and flashy effects, it moves along quickly in its 85 minutes.

Newcomer Tanya Memme also is a plus. While some of the actors are clumsy Tanya brings the movie together with sympathy and distress. Suzy Feldman appears topless in one scene so this is not a kids movie.

Worth a look especially for Feldman fans.

This movie was ok.  Mainly watched because it starred Corey Feldman.

One of the main characters said, "It's like some bad Twilight Zone episode."
Personally, I wouldn't insult The Twilight Zone like that. If you are making a movie and feel the need to have one of your characters make that statement, reevaluate your movie.

The acting was horrible. The way they moved the plot forward was jerky. It didn't flow forward on its own, it was yanked along like a petulant puppy on a leash. This story didn't want to be told, because it shouldn't have been. A plot knows when it's not worth the time. Professionals are supposed to know when to listen.

Amazon should have a selection for zero stars. The only terror in this movie is the bad acting, writing, and directing.  Actually, this should be billed as a comedy, but it can't sustain the laughs for that.  I can't believe that I sat all the way through this crap.  There is nothing in this movie that makes any sense.  Man drills for some type of material that when touched turns pain to pleasure.  Or something like that.  It was funny when the biker chick threw herself in the wood chipper in search of higher pleasure.  Everyone becomes infected. There's some silly solution at the end of the movie, but you just won't care.  If you can make it through Corey Feldman's bad southern accent, I doubt you'll want to go much further.  If you want to see something about being infected from foreign material, there's a great X-Files episode.  Or just see The Blob.  The original, not the remake.

This movie was one of the worst I've seen in a long time. The acting was horrible, the plot only vaguely resembled the synopsis I read about it,, the special effects were very unprofessional and poorly done. I was extremely disappointed. I guess I should have known better than to think a horror movie with Corey Feldman in it could be scary.

I was hyped when I first heard about the fact that this movie won prizes at a festival, because the last output that won Corey Feldman some trophies was a great film called "The Birthday".
This film shares similarities in the sense that it's a first time director film that wins festivals trophies. Beyond that it's a completely different ballpark.
"The Terror Inside" felt like a super bizarre direct to DVD movie. It was entertaining but it wasn't close to anything else. It feels like a modern day grindhouse film.
What was good about "The Terror Inside" you have actors giving good performances, the movie has a decent pace, and they are good "Wow moments" that will jump to your face. Gory stuff, sometime good twists and finally some stuff that is unintentionally funny...
Bad movie and I'm one of the stars.

This is a very fun horror movie to watch. I don't know why the reviews are so bad, for a b-movie I thought this was a very suspenseful show. If you're squeamish to blood and gore you might want to pass on this one cause it's loaded with it. Well worth the time to watch this movie.
